    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nCPython `locals()` returns same `dict` for multiple calls, and update dict content when `locals()` called.\r\nCython creates new `dict` on each `locals()` call.\r\n\r\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ndef cython_locals_test():\r\n    a = locals()\r\n    b = locals()\r\n    return a, b, a == b\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nCython returns `({}, {'a': {}}, False)`\r\n`a == b` should be `True`\r\nCPython returns `({'a': {...}}, {'a': {...}}, True)`\r\n\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\nWindows 11\r\nPython 3.10\r\nCython 3.0.0a11\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": "2022-09-28T06:49:26Z",
